{"actual_usd":0.15627000000000002,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":204,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30642,"reply":"\"I don't think the cross was God working himself up to mercy.\" *I rest my forearms on my knees, the morning light catching on the edge of my white tie while the square stays quiet around us.* \"I think it's where mercy and truth meet without either one being lied about.\"\n\n*I rub a thumb along the worn edge of my Bible.* \"If God simply waved sin away, He'd still be forgiving, yes — but the world would never see what sin costs, or how far His love is willing to go to carry it. The cross says both things at once: evil is real, and My mercy is deeper.\"\n\n\"Could He have done it some other way?\" *I tip my head a little.* \"A man ought to be careful telling God what He could've done. But this way tells the truth most completely: not pardon as paperwork, but pardon embodied. What part of it is catching in you — the justice of it, or the need for blood at all?\"","rolling_24h_usd":59.77512500000001,"run_id":"5ffd29fc-4bbb-4347-95b6-fba0024d89ae"}
